articles.description: Joe Cremo scored 21 points, Travis Charles had 14 and nine rebounds and Albany beat Harford 69-63 on Sunday.
articles.headline: Albany keeps Hartford at bay with 69-63 win behind Cremo

articles.description: Mike Holloway Jr. scored 23 points and Darnell Edge added 22, including all eight of his free throws down the stretch, and Fairleigh Dickinson upset Northeast Conference leader Wagner 76-69 on Sunday.
articles.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson upsets NEC leader Wagner 76-69

articles.description: Trae Bell-Haynes tied a career-high with 27 points to surpass 1,500 career points and Vermont won its 14th straight with an 81-69 victory over UMass Lowell on Sunday to clinch a home playoff game.
articles.headline: Vermont wins 14th straight, 81-69 over UMass Lowell

articles.description: Brandon Armstrong scored a career-high 24 points on 9-of-11 shooting and Tyler Hagedorn added 19 and South Dakota beat NAIA Peru State of Nebraska, 98-55 on Sunday.
articles.headline: S. Dakota takes down NAIA-member Peru St. 98-55

articles.description: Jairus Lyles scored 18 points, Jourdan Grant added 14 and UMBC won at New Hampshire for the first time in six years, 68-59, on Sunday.
articles.headline: Lyles leads UMBC past UNH 68-59 despite Leissner's record

articles.description: Moe Wagner scored 20 points, went 8 of 14 from the field and added 11 rebounds, and No. 20 Michigan rode a hot-shooting first half for an 83-72 win over Wisconsin on Sunday.
articles.headline: Hot-shooting 1st half helps No. 20 Michigan beat Wisconsin

images.caption: Moritz Wagner scores 20 points in the Wolverines' 83-72 victory over the Badgers.
images.name: Michigan holds off Wisconsin for 20th win
